The paper presents a data structure for sorted sets that supports searches, insertions, and deletions in sorted batches with optimal parallelism. This suggests that the paper belongs to the data structures (cs.DS) or parallel computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the PPM (parallel pointer machine) model, which is a theoretical model of parallel computation, indicating that the paper may also belong to the performance (cs.PF) or distributed computing (cs.Distributed) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions dynamic multithreading, which is a programming paradigm, suggesting that the paper may also belong to the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
